genresAdvancedInfo.name: corridos adictivos
genresAdvancedInfo.description: Corridos Adictivos is a popular music genre from Mexico that originated in the 19th century. It is a type of narrative ballad that tells stories of heroes, villains, and everyday people. The lyrics of the songs are often about love, betrayal, and violence. The music is characterized by the use of acoustic guitars, accordions, and trumpets. Corridos Adictivos is a popular genre among the Mexican working class and has been used as a tool for political and social commentary.
